description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse – Band 5 – Acute Assessment Unit – 37.5 hours per week – Permanent &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Could you help West Suffolk Hospital to deliver the best quality and safest care to our local community?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AAU is a blooming, innovative, front door service consisting of 23 assessment trolleys, one bay with cardiac monitoring facilities for higher dependency patients operating 24 hours a day. We have a dedicated multi-professional team accepting referrals from various Clinicians in the Community and Emergency Department, we accept patients with urgent medical needs.  Ambulatory Emergency Care Centre is also co-located to the Unit and provides same day assessment, treatment and discharge of appropriate medical and surgical patients. AAU/AEC is a very busy area with a wide variety of patients seeing on average 50 – 60 patients a day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud of our commitment to staff development. As an AAU Staff Nurse, the post holder will have the opportunity to work alongside our experienced team in emergency care in order to develop to provide fast paced, high standards of care and really make a positive impact to patients’ lives.  The experienced and supportive team on AAU &amp; AEC will assist with your integration, development and will offer you supernumerary time in order to get integrated into the Unit and the Multidisciplinary Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Registered Nurse the post holder will be in charge of a group of patients either in the AAU or the AEC co-working and supervising Assistant Practitioners and other members of staff in areas such as the Clinical Assessment &amp; Triage, AEC and performing various clinical skills: ECGs, Venepuncture, Cannulation, ABGs, Bladder Scans, Urinalyses. These are just a few of the many skills you will be able to learn and/or develop. The post holder will be expected to work a rotational shift pattern which means working 11 ½ hour shifts days, nights and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further enquiries please contact Michelle Rowley, Acute Assessment Unit Manager on 01284 713972 or via the email attached.&lt;/strong&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**In order to improve efficiency, all correspondence relating to this vacancy, &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;including invitations to interview will be by email only&lt;/span&gt;, via NHS Jobs. Would you therefore please ensure you check your emails on a regular basis**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In submitting an application form, you authorise West Suffolk NHS FT to confirm any previous NHS service details via the Inter Authority Transfer (IAT) process, should you be appointed to the post. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CAR PARKING&lt;/strong&gt; - This post &lt;strong&gt;does&lt;/strong&gt; entitle you to apply to park on the Hospital site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate for this post will be required to apply for a Disclosure &amp; Barring Service (DBS) Disclosure at Enhanced level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For Band 1 and Band 2 posts, the cost of the DBS Disclosure will be met by the Trust. However, any employees at Band 1 and Band 2 who leave the Trust within six months of commencing their post will have a £10 administration fee deducted from their final salary. For posts at Band 3 and above, the cost of the Disclosure will be met by the appointed employee and deducted in instalments from their salary over a period of three months. If the employee leaves the Trust within three months of commencing their post, any outstanding payments will be deducted from their final pay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants should click on the link entitled “How will my application be processed?” prior to submitting their application form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date for this vacancy may change if we receive a strong response. Please ensure that you apply for any post you are interested in as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
